As the ImportError is meant to suggest, you lack the qtconsole package:

```
conda install qtconsole
```

then launch with

```
jupyter qtconsole
```

I tried your instruction:
The qtconsole package had already installed.

```

dell@DELL-PC C:\Users\dell
> conda install qtconsole
Fetching package metadata: ....
Solving package specifications: ..........
# All requested packages already installed.
# packages in environment at C:\MyPrograms\Anaconda3:
#
qtconsole                 4.0.1                    py34_0

dell@DELL-PC C:\Users\dell
> jupyter qtconsole
jupyter: 'qtconsole' is not a Jupyter command

dell@DELL-PC C:\Users\dell
```
Hm, not sure why I didn't see it the first time. What does `python -m qtconsole` do?

Hmm, may be something wrong...

```
dell@DELL-PC C:\Users\dell
> python -m qtconsole
C:\MyPrograms\Anaconda3\python.exe: No module named qtconsole.__main__; 'qtconsole' is a package and cannot be directly executed

dell@DELL-PC C:\Users\dell
>
```
Hm, that suggests a broken installation, since it certainly is not true. Can you remove and reinstall the qtconsole package, perhaps?
Closing as it's probably not a bug in IPython. Feel free to continue using the comments for troubleshooting.
